{
  "texts": [
    "Running GPT-4 on the development set took approximately 102 min, GPT-3.5 took 48 min.",
    "Running Llama-2 took 50 h, and running SDL2 on the development set took 66 h. However, these numbers are subject to change, as LLMs are continuously improving in speed, and both Llama-2 and SDL2 can now be hosted in the cloud as well.",
    "Performance on test sets Fig. 3 illustrates the performance of human reviewers compared to the optimal prompt strategies applied to GPT-4 and SDL2.",
    "When evaluated against the gold standard for test set 1, LLMs demonstrate similar levels of sensitivity and specificity to those of human reviewers.",
    "In test set 2, LLMs show higher sensitivity, though their specificity falls at the lower range of human performance."
  ]
}